  In the given code, `Barrier` is used to synchronize tasks that are dependent on each other. A barrier ensures that all tasks waiting at a barrier have completed before proceeding with the next task.

  The main purpose of using a barrier in this context is to prevent the main thread from continuing until all the worker threads have finished their work. This helps in avoiding potential race conditions and ensures that the result is accurate.

